    - Error Recurrence Rate: < 5%
    - User Error Exposure: < 0.1%

# =============================================================================
# PURGING PERIOD (Retinol Side Effect)
# =============================================================================
PURGING_EXPLANATION:
  What_Is_Purging:
    - Temporary increase in visible errors
    - Occurs when using Retinol (code refactoring)
    - Brings deep issues to surface
    - Actually a sign the treatment is working
    - Should resolve within 4-6 weeks
    
  Why_It_Happens:
    - Refactoring exposes hidden bugs
    - Increased test coverage finds more issues
    - Improved monitoring detects problems earlier
    - Technical debt being addressed systematically
    
  How_To_Manage:
    - Expect it: Plan for temporary increase in errors
    - Monitor closely: Track error trends
    - Stay consistent: Don't stop treatment
    - Protect users: Use feature flags and gradual rollout
    - Communicate: Team and stakeholder awareness
    - Be patient: Benefits come after purging
    
  When_To_Worry:
    - Purging lasts > 8 weeks
    - Error rate increases > 200%
    - Critical errors emerge
    - User experience significantly degraded
    → Reduce Retinol strength or pause treatment

# =============================================================================
# WARNINGS & PRECAUTIONS
# =============================================================================
WARNINGS:
  General:
    - Patch test first (pilot in dev/staging)
    - Start with lower concentration
    - Increase strength gradually
    - May cause purging (temporary error increase)
    - Some dryness normal (alert notifications)
    - Discontinue if severe irritation (system instability)
    
  Benzoyl_Peroxide_Warnings:
    - Bleaches fabric (can corrupt data if misused)
    - Start with 2.5%, increase if needed
    - May cause initial dryness (alert fatigue)
    - Use only on affected areas (targeted fixes)
    
  Retinol_Warnings:
    - Start with 0.1-0.3%, build to 1.0%
    - Use only at night (off-peak refactoring)
    - Expect purging period (4-6 weeks)
    - Increase sun sensitivity (more vulnerable during refactoring)
    - Not for pregnant systems (major migrations in progress)
    - Dermatologist supervision recommended (senior engineer oversight)
    
  Salicylic_Acid_Warnings:
    - Can be drying (excessive logging overhead)
    - Don't over-exfoliate (don't over-analyze)
    - Avoid if allergic (incompatible with certain architectures)

# =============================================================================
# CONTRAINDICATIONS
# =============================================================================
CONTRAINDICATIONS:
  - Severe system instability (repair first with scar-repair.skn)
  - Allergic to error handling (legacy systems that can't change)
  - During major migrations (wait for stability)
  - Real-time critical systems (unacceptable latency)
  - Insufficient monitoring infrastructure
  - Lack of rollback capability
  - Production without testing environments

# =============================================================================
# ANALOGIES (AGI Construct Mapping)
# =============================================================================
ANALOGY: exception_resolution.scm

ALEXANDER_PATTERN: "Good Shape" - Problems as opportunities for improvement
ALEXANDER_PRINCIPLES:
  - Good Shape: Each error reveals improvement opportunity
  - Diagnose First: Understand before treating
  - Minimal Intervention: Smallest effective fix
  - Learn and Adapt: System strengthens from each error
  - Systemic Thinking: Fix root causes, not symptoms

AGI_COMPONENTS:
  - Problem Detection: Acne identification
  - Isolation: Quarantine and containment
  - Treatment: Error resolution strategies
  - Learning Loop: Prevent recurrence
  - Prevention: Skincare routine for healthy code

ACNE_SCIENCE_PARALLEL:
  Acne_Formation → Error_Creation:
    - Clogged Pores: Poor input validation
    - Bacteria: Bugs in code
    - Inflammation: Error propagation
    - Hormones: Environmental triggers (load, resources)
    - Stress: Technical debt accumulation
    
  Treatment_Mechanisms:
    - Salicylic Acid: Root cause analysis
    - Benzoyl Peroxide: Bug elimination
    - Retinol: Code modernization
    - Tea Tree Oil: Test coverage
    - Niacinamide: Error boundaries
    
  Prevention_vs_Treatment:
    - Prevention: Better than cure (input validation, testing)
    - Spot Treatment: Fast targeted fixes
    - Systemic: Address root causes (architecture)
    - Professional: Expert help for severe cases

