# =============================================================================
# EXPERT TIPS (Dermatologist Recommendations)
# =============================================================================
PROFESSIONAL_ADVICE:
  - Don't squeeze: Resist quick hacks, proper fixes take time
  - Be consistent: Daily routine > occasional heroics
  - Patience: Clear skin (stable system) takes months
  - Less is more: Don't over-treat (alert fatigue)
  - Professional help: Severe acne needs expert (architects)
  - Prevention: Better than treatment (testing > debugging)
  - Hydrate: Maintain context and logging
  - Sleep: Give systems rest (maintenance windows)

COMMON_MISTAKES:
  - Over-treating (too many tools, alert fatigue)
  - Inconsistent routine (sporadic error handling)
  - Squeezing (hasty fixes without analysis)
  - Giving up early (during purging period)
  - Wrong products (inappropriate error handling)
  - Skipping sunscreen (neglecting security)
  - Not moisturizing (inadequate logging/context)

